## Transaction Rules

### When to Use Transactions

**Always use `$transaction` for:**

```typescript
// Character creation (creates user + character)
await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
  const user = await tx.user.create({ data: { discordId, username } });
  await tx.character.create({ data: { userId: user.id, ... } });
});

// Cultivation (update character + create log + update cooldown)
await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
  await tx.character.update({ where: { id }, data: { cultivationPoints: { increment: points } } });
  await tx.cultivationSession.create({ data: { characterId: id, ... } });
  await tx.actionLog.create({ data: { characterId: id, action: "CULTIVATE", ... } });
});

// Admin action (update character + create audit log)
await prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => {
  await tx.character.update({ where: { id }, data: { silver: { increment: amount } } });
  await tx.adminAuditLog.create({ data: { adminId, action: "ITEM_GIVE", ... } });
});
```

### Race Condition Prevention

**Cooldowns:**

```typescript
// WRONG: Check then update (race condition)
const existing = await prisma.cooldown.findUnique({ where: { characterId_type: { characterId, type } } });
if (existing && existing.expiresAt > new Date()) throw new Error("Cooldown active");
await prisma.cooldown.upsert({ ... }); // Another request could insert between check and upsert!

// RIGHT: Upsert with condition
await prisma.cooldown.upsert({
  where: { characterId_type: { characterId, type } },
  create: { characterId, type, expiresAt },
  update: {
    where: { characterId_type: { characterId, type } },
    data: { expiresAt }, // Only update if the upsert itself succeeds
  },
});
```

**Currency/Inventory:**

```typescript
// WRONG: Read then write
const char = await prisma.character.findUnique({ where: { id } });
if (char.silver < cost) throw new Error("Not enough silver");
await prisma.character.update({ where: { id }, data: { silver: { decrement: cost } } });

// RIGHT: Update with condition
const result = await prisma.character.updateMany({
  where: { id, silver: { gte: cost } },
  data: { silver: { decrement: cost } },
});
if (result.count === 0) throw new Error("Not enough silver");
```

