## Seed Data Rules

### What Goes in Seeds

| Category | Examples |
|----------|----------|
| Realms | 10 cultivation realms |
| Regions | 8 geographic regions |
| Sects | 50 sects (with names, alignment, rank) |
| Items | 30 starting items |
| Manuals | 20 starting cultivation techniques |
| Alchemy recipes | 10 base recipes |
| Encounters | 30 encounter templates |
| World events | 5 initial event templates |

### Seed File Organization

```
packages/db/prisma/
├── schema.prisma
├── seed.ts              # Full seed: realms + regions + sects + items + manuals + recipes + encounters
└── seeds/
    ├── realms.seed.ts   # Optional: split seeds for cleaner management
    ├── regions.seed.ts
    ├── sects.seed.ts
    ├── items.seed.ts
    └── ...
```

### Seed Best Practices

```typescript
// Use upsert to make seeds idempotent
await prisma.realm.upsert({
  where: { order: 1 },
  update: { /* keep existing */ },
  create: { id: "LUYEN_THE", name: "Luyện Thể", order: 1, ... },
});

// Wrap in try-catch with descriptive error
try {
  await seedRealms();
} catch (error) {
  throw new Error(`Failed to seed realms: ${error instanceof Error ? error.message : error}`);
}
```

