## Query Patterns

### Fetching Character with Relations

```typescript
// Always eager-load what you need
const character = await prisma.character.findUnique({
  where: { id },
  include: {
    realm: true,
    region: true,
    sect: true,
    manual: true,
    inventories: { include: { item: true } },
  },
});

// Convert to plain object for core engine
const characterState: CharacterState = {
  id: character.id,
  name: character.name,
  realm: character.realmId as RealmId,
  cultivationPoints: character.cultivationPoints,
  // ... all fields
  // Note: Prisma relation fields are nested objects, core expects flat structure
};
```

### Pagination

```typescript
// For large result sets
const page = Math.max(1, pageParam ?? 1);
const pageSize = Math.min(50, pageSizeParam ?? 20);

const results = await prisma.actionLog.findMany({
  where: { characterId },
  orderBy: { createdAt: "desc" },
  skip: (page - 1) * pageSize,
  take: pageSize,
  include: { character: { select: { name: true } } },
});
```

